caption: Great food! Very nice atmosphere for a date.

Ordered online for pickup. Food was waiting when I arrived. The lady that rang me out was super nice & friendly! I ordered the sweet & sour chicken & chicken fried rice, both were excellent!! Love that the sweet & sour chicken is light & crunchy but not greasy. Can't wait to order again!

The quality at JJ's has dropped substantially since Covid.  Very little meat, lots of vegetables.  They should probably close. I just bought kung pao chicken and there are so many carrots I could not find the little meat. It was $20 and I picked it up by foot.  Never mind. I am done with this place.

Love this place!!!  EDIT:  4 months later and I still love this place.  My wife is allergic to gluten. So Hui lets me keep our own GF soy sauce  on hand for whenever my wife wants me to bring home Chinese.  Edit: April 2021 and I still love this place.
I love it here I hope they never close!!!

Carryout and appetizer review: this place was super cute. Indoor dining was closed due to the pandemic. I ordered in person and had a lovely conversation with the lady upfront. She is such a gem! My rolls were buttery and flaky, and my …

Best Chinese food in Denver. The food is always amazing no matter what I order! If you’re doing delivery, order directly through them. Way faster and more professional than any other delivery service. You won’t regret ordering from JJs!
Wings are amazing! Super crispy and saucy. Hot and sour soup is light and not gloppy at all and very well seasoned. Delicious.
Love this place, I will definitely have gatherings here.
Take out only as of 1/24/21. Friendly staff, good new York style Chinese food. Sushi menu is on hold for the moment, so I can't comment on that.

We checked out JJ’s recently as a we live right across the street from Sakura Square and we LOVE IT! Feels very authentic/family owned and the prices are terrific! We ordered the family dinner special and got two entrees, two soups, spring …
Love this place. Very ma and pop spot. A definite 5 star+ must visit!
Love JJs! The owners are wonderful!! Always so welcoming to my kiddos!! Only place I'll go for Chinese food!
Literally the best Chinese I’ve ever had and the hospitality was beyond amazing!! She was the sweetest soul!! 10/10 would recommend!!!

They have become my GO TO for Chinese food cravings! Every time I've tried something new, its been delicious and fresh. Tangerine  chicken is always one of my favorites ... super nice folks that own it.
A great hidden gem! Everything we tried was delicious. And my boyfriend says their cheese wontons are the best he's had! Can't go wrong here.

Service is outstanding. I was having a horrible day, but the friendly wait staff really did a great job at lifting my spirits.  I wish I could say the same about the food. I ordered a chicken with broccoli. Simple enough, right? The chicken …
The nicest management around and the food is AMAZING!!! Very well priced and delicious!

Reasonably priced, fast, hot, DELICIOUS, and friendly!! We enjoyed chatting with the owner as we picked up our order and she had a really safe and efficient setup for pickup. The portions are generous and everything is so good - definitely get veggie spring rolls!

Great food

Best chinese food I've ever had, and best restaurant experience. Pouring down rain when we went so it was deserted, and the owner and staff came by to chat with us and make us feel welcome!

I enjoyed myself so much at this place! The food is espectacular but nothing tops a hard working family that is willing to give you the best service! I will certainly call this place home whenever I travel back to Denver!

This will be the best Chinese food you will find in Denver! The quality of there food is unbelievable and so tasty. I have been here many times and everytime does not disappoint.

Best place in town!

Typical east coast Chinese food! Great service and attentive waitress! She was quite pleasant to talk to. The food was fantastic as well. Can't beat the price given the location either.
Not a bad little joint for your run of the mill Chinese food.

This is honestly THE best chinese food Ive had in a long time. Like sure there's Panda Express and other local restaurants, but JJ Bistro just wiped the floor out of all of them. Not to mention excellent customer service, and really nice people here. If Im ever near by Im gonna stop by all the time.
Food was not good. The woman server was very attentive and gave good service.
Great food. Quiet place. It's on the second floor so if you're feeling lost that may be why.

I was able to order online and the Shrimp Fried Rice was really good. The lunch special included an egg role and a crab cheese wanton. One important note, THIS RESTAURANT IS ON THE SECOND FLOOR! I spent ten minutes wandering around Sakura Square looking for this place
The food is great I would recommend this place for good Chinese food

General Tso's Chicken was both overpriced (compared to similar places in the neighborhood) and of poor quality.  Making up the lower quality evaluation was no vegetables in the mix and soggy tempura coating that seemed more like a breading coating that had soaked up the bland sauce.
Great classic east coast Chinese food. Good food,clean,well priced,nice owner snd,staff plus tatsty food. Great combo Tasty tasty 😃😃
Bomb old school American Chinese food at killer prices.
Good tasting food!!
Great food and some of the best service I’ve ever had anywhere. I was in Denver for a volleyball tournament my daughter and I walked over from hotel. The lady working there was so friendly and kind.

Finally, I’ve discovered a great NY-style Chinese place in Denver. The food is better than its next competitor, Great Wall on Colfax, and the service is head and shoulders above. The lunch special gets you an entree, soup and egg roll for less than nine bucks.

I love this place so much! The pastries are amazing and the atmosphere is so cozy. This location closed early 2018, but they opened a new location called Tiny Pyramid. I'm so excited to eat their desserts again!
Nice lunch place, and they know how to make it very spicy. Service is excellent!
So sad.  Menu right out of the 80s to match the decor.  Food just as blah.  Sometimes these out-of-the-way mom & pops are gems, sometimes they're just waiting to die.  This one is ready for hospice.
great food, great service
We were here Christmas Day and enjoyed every moment of it. Looked a little run down but the food was great. I am coming back for more.

Excellent service & decent food. Orange chicken was a little too tangy.

First off, this place is on the second floor. I almost left the area because I didn’t realize this. The food is great and the owner is very friendly. Don’t miss out on this place.

This is a great little place to grab some affordable fresh Chinese food. The staff is attentive and friendly. If you have time to kill the sushi is great too.
Great food and the lady who runs it is extremely nice and funny. You couldn't find a sweeter person.
Amazing food and the service is amazing as well.  They had a good selection of vegitarian dishes as well.  Generous portions as well.  5 stars!

Great hidden gem.  High quality downtown Asian food, but at lower than downtown prices!

Ordered takeout veggie fried rice. They were very accommodating to my vegan needs and were very sweet and friendly when I went to pick it up. Tasted great and the large portion was well worth the price!

Service is great the good is great too but the price when you dine in is cheap, I will be going back many times. Thank you

One of the best dining experiences of my life family owned and operated love them end of story you would simply be stupid not to come here

Awful! I'm never getting a delivery order from here ever again. I ordered a boba drink and some miso soup. My order came without a spoon or straw to actually drink my boba.When I called to get my spoon and straw back I was given serious …
This place has been around for a long time, and the food that I order is very consistent. If you like them once, then you will like them forever!
Fantastic food and service. Their food is always fresh and cooked properly and it is full of flavor. One of my favorite Asian restaurants that I've been to in Denver.

My Favorite Chinese Restaurant in Denver, and I order from here several times a month. Always fresh and flavorful food. Extremely nice staff. Fast, accurate and friendly delivery. The bad reviews must be from the competition, because in six years I've NEVER had a bad meal from JJ's.
Some people love it and some people hate it. I think it's great food. The lady there knows me and is very friendly.
Love this place, local business and many veggie options. The owner is so sweet.
Good service and great food. Great for a quick lunch.

Ordered the sesame chicken, lunch special.  It was amazingly quick.  It was super quiet for a lunch.  Construction kind of turned me off, it was a little weird to get to but totally worth it.  Chicken tasted fresh and crunchy, made-to-order, not sitting in a heat lamp waiting for customer.

The food is extremely fresh nothing is frozen it's all made fresh she and her husband are terrific cooks no msg ever!  One of downtown Denver's longest Chinese restaurants for a reason The food is good!
I'm a big fan of this place, got delivery all the time here!  Solid pricing and great food.

Holy cow! Order it extra spicy!!! On a 1-5, ask for 4! It'll melt your face off :)  Real habaneros my friends

Went in on a Saturday afternoon and we were served very quickly. Best Chinese food I've ever eaten. Ordered the Hot and Sour soup first and it is literally the best hot and sour soup that has ever entered my mouth, Followed was an appetizer …
This is a mom and popshop, if ever there was one. Really nice family, serving very affordable Chinese food. The lunch sets are great. Oneof my favorite items is the seafood hot and sour soup, yum!

And when I asked if I could just cancel the order, the woman sounded greatful and thanked me for canceling.  All because I wanted to add broccoli to my fried rice.  6:20pm Monday October 5th, 2015 Very bad business practice.

Seriously THE BEST Chinese food. Chinese is my absolute favorite, and it only took one time eating here for me to be addicted. All the battered and fried protein isn't over cooked. It's actually juicy meat not just fried batter. The Crab Ragoons and Fried Dumplings are to die for. SO So glad I found this place. No more searching.
great service and food was good. Only 10 including tip

The staff here was very friendly and the food was good. The restaurant entrance was a little hard to find. This is a good place for lunch on a work day.
Great value on the lunch menu. Their chinese selection tasted better than the rolls. All in all, your typically good chinese spot.
